<TITLE> Ctg airport security beefed up too </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, April 9 (bdnews24.com)  Following Dhaka, security measures have been beefed up at Chittagong airport over a hijack alert on Friday. Security at Shahjalal International Airport in Dhaka was heightened over speculations of possible hijacking and terrorist activity on Thursday. Ohid Ullah, officer in charge (immigration) of Chittagong Shah Amanat International Airport told bdnews24.com on Friday morning that security measures have been beefed up at the airport and RAB-police patrol have been increased. Dhaka airport officials requested for extra security from the police Thursday night. Officer in charge of Shahjalal International Airport Police Station told bdnews24.com that security measures had been increased. He also said that decision to boost security came after receiving information from the intelligence agency regarding the threat. Newspapers reported that security was beefed up after the US Federal Bureau of Investigation alerted about the threat. bdnews2
